<br>
For those that are wondering about anti-spam code, and how it effects /pet back off and other /pet commands being spammed repeatedly, try this little trick.<br>
<br>
/pet target  (always targets your pet instantly, this is client side)<br>
/ttell follow me<br>
<br>
And you will see: Jobaner says, 'Following you Master'<br>
<br>
What does this mean?<br>
<br>
/pet commands are actually sent via the game's /tell mechanism, though without the fairly recent addition of the /ttell command used on a pre-targeted pet, you can't just /tell Jobaner (the pets real name is probably Jobaner04234, but the game engine hides the rest), so most players don't know this, even pet classes.<br>
<br>
Also, when pets are created, they are set so they only listen to and respond to their masters tells, so you can't target a friends pet and /ttell report health to spam them to death, it just won't do anything. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Now, as for the anti-spam code... you can only send 1 tell to the same target once every 3 or 4 seconds.  This is a limitation/restriction set on the /tell function.<br>
<br>
Try this with a friend, either via a hotkey or by rapidly recalling the last line in the scrollbox and editing it.<br>
<br>
/tell Friend A<br>
/tell Friend B<br>
/tell Friend C<br>
/tell Friend D<br>
/tell Friend E<br>
<br>
See how many your client actually sends.  Each line is different, so it's not blocking repitition.  You will find it's only sending every second or third (depending on whether you hotkey it, or type it manually)<br>
<br>
So in summary, /pet is a modified, pet pre-targeted specific version of /tell, and falls into the same filtering categories.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Kantreach</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Orb weilding Gnome Arch Magi</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Tholuxe Paells</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
PS: One other useless game mechanic tip... NPC's respond to text in one of two forms.  A specific phrase, or a list of code words.  If they need a specific phrase, you have to say the whole senance in the correct order or it won't work.  If they just respond to a list of code words, you can put the words in any order in a sentance, and you only need to use the first 4 letters.<br>
<br>
Confused?  Next time you Hail the Nexus Scion, try &quot;/say to lucl jour&quot;  and try to figure out why she still hands you the gem. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uansifiretosser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ansi Firetosser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 262<br> <font color=#333333>(5/23/02 3:28:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Pet Discipline</span><hr size=1> Kantreach,<br>
